title: Comedian dreamed up likes and dislikes for homeless cats | Daily Mail Online
text: show ad 'Dislikes: The warlock's curse that turned her into a cat': Comedian gives homeless felines at animal shelter lists of interests to help them get adopted Jeff Wysaski, the comedian behind Obvious Plant, created funny signs for cats at the Sant√© D'Or Foundation animal rescue He assigned them obvious interests, like laying in the sun and playing with toys The 'dislikes' were more surprising, like 'fart jokes' and 'when jazz musicians call each other cats' Published: 20:33 GMT, 20 February 2017 | Updated: 20:36 GMT, 20 February 2017 8 shares
